{"title":"Josh&#8217;s Albums of the Year","link":"https://kottke.org/24/11/joshs-albums-of-the-year","date":1732294362000,"content":"\n        <p>My friend <a href=\"https://www.wildflower.family\">Josh LaFayette</a> spends the very last part of the year making fan art for his <a href=\"https://www.joshlafayette.com/bestalbums\">favorite albums of the year</a> and despite all the pieces being visually different there’s a through line which make all of them immediately recognizable to me as his art. He’s putting out <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/joshlafayette\">a few a week on his Instagram</a>, but I grabbed these two because I also loved these albums. </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://johnmoreland.bandcamp.com/album/visitor\">John Moreland - Visitor</a></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/John%20Moreland%20-%20Vistor%20copy.jpeg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/John%20Moreland%20-%20Vistor%20copy.jpeg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/John%20Moreland%20-%20Vistor%20copy.jpeg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3000\" height=\"3750\" alt=\"John Moreland - Vistor copy.jpeg\" /></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://laurajanegrace.bandcamp.com/album/hole-in-my-head\">Laura Jane Grace’s - Hole in My Head</a></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/LauraJaneGrace-HoleInMyHead.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/LauraJaneGrace-HoleInMyHead.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/LauraJaneGrace-HoleInMyHead.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"3125\" alt=\"LauraJaneGrace-HoleInMyHead.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>My favorite part of this series is all of the pieces are physical, not just a file on the computer. Every piece is a reference to the design language present in the age of accessible digital printing—they’re inspired by what some might call “naïve” or “uniformed” designs that are common in the American visual vernacular. The Moreland piece is a take on the flyers for psychics you see all over and the LJG piece is your favorite hippie soap.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/John%20Moreland%20Flyer.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/John%20Moreland%20Flyer.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/John%20Moreland%20Flyer.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2014\" height=\"2518\" alt=\"John Moreland Flyer.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/LJG.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/LJG.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/LJG.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2213\" height=\"2766\" alt=\"LJG.jpg\" /></p>\n\n        \n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/art\">art</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/John%20Moreland\">John Moreland</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Josh%20LaFayette\">Josh LaFayette</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Laura%20Jane%20Grace\">Laura Jane Grace</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/music\">music</a></p>\n\n         <p>💬 <a href=\"https://kottke.org/24/11/joshs-albums-of-the-year\">Join the discussion on kottke.org</a> →</p>\n\n    ","author":"Aaron Cohen","siteTitle":"Kottke","siteHash":"89a883271b4598f9b33ebe87be70d38557bcd266e68aee521a8f93622e0ab723","entryHash":"488e236b0c4f62bc64e1b8625bd418805f50b2ad80c23b851689a0489d716f40","category":"Sites"}